      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MITCHELLS RUN (1) is hard to knock having put two wins together. Had to call on all reserves to salute at the most recent appearance over 947m at this track, getting home by 1.2 metres. Gets the ace draw so can keep the ball rolling. KONNYMARA (2) has been competitive of late and added to his consistent form when he came from the back row last time for fourth at Albion Park. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw. Finds a nice race and can discover winning form. ROLLYARRRZ NZ (8) draws on the back row but drops to a distance where he owns a good record and is on the radar after his last-start fourth here week ago. BARRETT (9) should find this easier than the latest attempt at Albion Park.",
